The '''White-crested Guan''' ('''''Penelope pileata''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the [[Cracidae]] family, the [[chachalaca]]s, [[guan (bird)|guan]]s, and [[curassow]]s.
It is found only in regions of the southeast [[Amazon Basin]] of [[Brazil]]. The species is restricted to the southern riverbank of the [[Amazon River]]; also eastwards, the south bank of the [[Par<U+00E1> River]] south of [[Maraj<U+00F3>|Maraj<U+00F3> Island]] at the Amazon River's outlet. 
Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s.
It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].
